						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone standing in Survey No. 36.</hi></p>						

						<p>(Date lost).</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged and mutilated inscription is engraved in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">10th century.</hi> Only the letters <hi rend="italic">Varisha,</hi> apparently the last part of the name of a <hi rend="bold">Rāshṭrakūṭa</hi> king, are preserved. It seems to register a gift of land. <hi rend="bold">Banavāsi Twelvethousand</hi> is mentioned. A <hi rend="bold">Chaḷuki</hi> chief named <hi rend="bold">Ayyappa</hi> is also mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
